# AI Builder Knowledge Base (`lib/ai/builder-knowledge-v2.ts`)

The AI builder is a **multi-agent pipeline**. The system prompt in `builder-knowledge-v2.ts` is the static "tool manual" that orchestrators and free-form chat use. Per-scope sub-agents (Structure, Binding, UI / Styling, Animation, Workflow, Data, Media) carry their own focused prompts under `lib/ai/agents/<scope>/prompt.ts`.

---

## Tool Manual Principle — What the AI Needs vs What Is Leakage

The system prompt is a **tool manual**, not a design guide. Claude already knows how to design. The four things the AI needs that it cannot derive from general knowledge:

| Category | Examples | Where it lives |
|---|---|---|
| **1. Tool names + input parameters** | `set_style(id, {...})`, `set_layout(id, {gap})`, `set_animation(id, {tilt: {...}})` | `builder-tools.ts` schema + per-agent prompts |
| **2. System-specific behavior** | Token names, `{{variables['UUID']}}` formula syntax, JS bindings `{ js: "<body>" }`, responsive cascade | `JSON_SCHEMA_RULES`, knowledge blocks |
| **3. Component primitives + structure** | The 8 real primitives (Box, Text, Input, Textarea, Image, Icon, Video, Iframe); shared components; loop templates | `COMPONENT_AI_REFS` (names + summaries in code), `PRIMITIVES_BLOCK`, `SHARED_COMPONENTS_BLOCK` |
| **4. System quirks** | Drag/swipe gesture payload, JS forbidden tokens, batch nodeId ordering, theme color tokens | knowledge blocks + agent prompts |

**Diagnostic rule:** When AI output is wrong, the fix is either (a) extend the tool to support the capability, or (b) add one system-specific fact. **Never add design guidance** — Claude already knows how to design.

**What is leakage (never put in what the AI sees):**
- General design principles (contrast theory, layout patterns, when to use rounded corners)
- Tailwind class names (`flex-col`, `w-full`, `text-gray-900`, `rounded-lg`, `p-4`, …)
- Raw JSON node structure (`className`, `style`, `props`, `children` keys)
- CSS terminology (`align-items`, `justify-content`, `flex-1`, …)
- Internal prop names (`props.src`, `props.icon`, `props.type`)
- Tool write targets (`→ style.opacity`, `→ style.transform`, …)
- Implementation details about how tools store values internally

**Rule for new content:** Before adding anything to `builder-knowledge-v2.ts`, ask: "Is this something Claude cannot know without being told?" If Claude can derive it from general design/CSS/engineering knowledge, it does not belong in the system prompt.

