## Multi-Agent Architecture

Every user message unconditionally routes to `runBuildPipeline()` in `lib/ai/agents/dispatch.ts` — there is no Phase-0 classifier, no `BuildPlan`, and no edit loop. The **Planner** decides what to do via the `ContractManifest`.

| Agent | ID in registry | Tools | Prompt |
|---|---|---|---|
| Context Agent (Haiku) | — | `search`, `semantic_search`, `read` | `lib/ai/agents/context-agent.ts` |
| Planner (Haiku, single-shot) | — | emits `ContractManifest` (ops + `sharedComponentsToCreate`) | `agents/planner/prompt.ts` |
| Structure (deterministic, no LLM) | `structure` | `generate_structure`, `add_variable` | `agents/structure/structure-step.ts` |
| UI / Styling (Haiku) | `styling` | `set_style` | `agents/layout/prompt.ts` (`buildStylingAgentPrompt`) |
| Animation (Haiku) | `animation` | `set_animation` | `agents/animation/prompt.ts` |
| Workflows (Haiku) | `workflows` | `create_workflow`, `bind_action`, `update_workflow_steps`, `set_workflow_params` | `agents/workflows/prompt.ts` |
| Data (Haiku) | `data` | `add_data_source`, `update_data_source`, `delete_data_source` | `agents/data/prompt.ts` |
| Binding (Haiku) | `binding` | `set_text`, `set_repeat`, `set_condition`, `set_disabled`, `set_src`, `set_icon_src` | `agents/binding/prompt.ts` |
| Media (Haiku) | `media` | `search_images`, `search_videos`, `search_icons`, `set_src`, `set_background`, `set_icon_src` | `agents/media/prompt.ts` |
| Shared Components (Haiku) | `sharedComponents` | SC model edits via `enter_shared_component_edit` / `exit_shared_component_edit` | `agents/sharedComponents/prompt.ts` |

**Hard invariants:**
- Only the **Structure** step creates resources (pages, nodes, variables, workflows, data sources, SC instances). Every UUID downstream agents reference must already exist in the manifest.
- Structure processes **`sharedComponentsToCreate` BEFORE pages** — SC models (with `_sharedKey`-stamped internal nodes) are fully ready before any specialist agent starts.
- Within a build, all specialists (styling / animation / binding / workflows / data / media / sharedComponents) **run in parallel** in a single flat `Promise.all` pool — they never collide because Structure pre-mints all UUIDs.

**SC three-path instance overrides (page agents):**
- Path 1: `set_component_props(instanceId, { propName })` — declared property override
- Path 2: `set_style/set_animation/set_text(internalNodeId, ...)` — targets a specific node inside this instance via `_sharedKey`
- Path 3: `set_style(instanceId, ...)` — styles the instance's root Box wrapper

**`sharedComponents` agent scope:** Model edits only, runs on a separate user-intent turn. Never runs during builds that create new SCs (the planner authors those inline).

