## Style Mechanism Map (current tools)

The styling toolset was consolidated in Phase B. There is now **one** unified styling tool (`set_style`) plus a focused `set_layout` for direction/justify/align/gap.

| Tool | Mechanism | Units |
|---|---|---|
| `set_style` (unified) | `props.className` (arbitrary-value Tailwind for pixels, tokens for fixed enums) + `props.style` for opacity/rotate; strips conflicting style/class on every write | pixels (numbers) and token strings — mirrors the panel exactly |
| `set_layout` | `props.className` for direction/justify/align/grid + `gap-[Npx]`; strips `style.gap` | pixels for gap; token strings for direction/justify/align |
| `set_background` | `props.className` (bg-[color] class) + strips `style.backgroundColor` | color string or `theme:tokenName` |
| `set_animation` | `node.animation.*` object (nested config for tilt/parallax/drag/gesture/states/etc.) | enum strings + nested objects matching `AnimationConfig` |
| `set_validation` | `node.validation.*` array of `{type, message, value, formula}` | enum + string |
| `set_repeat` | `node.repeat = { source, key }` formula | formula expression |
| `set_condition` | `node.showIf` formula | formula expression |
| `set_responsive_override` | `node.responsive[bp].<field>` | per-field |
| `bind_action` | `node.actions[i] = { workflowId, trigger? }` | trigger enum string + workflow id |
| `set_text` / `set_placeholder` / `set_src` / `set_icon_src` | direct prop / formula | string or `{ formula }` / `{ js }` |

**Runtime rendering note:** Arbitrary-value Tailwind classes written from JSON (e.g. `pt-[96px]`, `bg-[#0f172a]`) are not compiled by NativeWind's static scanner. The renderer's `classToInlineStyle()` in `lib/sdui/renderer.tsx` converts them at render time. JSON stores classes (for panel sync), browser sees inline styles.

**Removed tools (do not reference):** `set_class`, `set_grid`, `set_typography`, `set_spacing`, `set_position`, `set_size`, `set_border`, `set_shadow`, `set_text_color`, `get_formula_context`, `get_components`. All folded into `set_style` / `set_layout` / `set_animation`.

