## How the System Prompt Is Built

`buildChatSystemPrompt(context)` in `lib/ai/builder-knowledge-v2.ts` is called per-request and returns the full system prompt string. It injects:

- `paletteSnapshot` — live resolved CSS variable values (var=hex pairs) so the AI knows the current theme
- `currentPageName`, `pages`, `selectedNodeSummary` — per-request builder state
- Component list (auto-derived from `COMPONENT_AI_REFS` — the 8 real primitives)
- All tool descriptions and quick reference
- Concept blocks: `PRIMITIVES_BLOCK`, `SHARED_COMPONENTS_BLOCK`, `RESPONSIVE_BLOCK`, `TRIGGERS_BLOCK`, `AUTH_BLOCK`, `JS_FORMULAS_BLOCK`, `ACTION_CATALOG_BLOCK`, `MOTION_BLOCK`

**Injection order:**
1. Project context (appName, description, category, mood)
2. Builder context (current page, selected node)
3. Capability reference table (auto-generated from `COMPONENT_CAPABILITIES`)
4. Primitives, Shared Components, Responsive, Triggers, Auth, JS-in-formulas, Action catalog, Motion blocks
5. Formula function library (auto-generated from `FUNCTION_LIBRARY`)
6. Theme block (live palette)

**Never hardcode theme values** — they come from `paletteSnapshot` at runtime.

